# Public Complaint App (Aplikasi Pengaduan Masyarakat)

This document outlines the technical plan for building a robust public complaint system with real-time tracking, GPS integration, and automated escalation to government agencies (SKPD).

## System Architecture

The application will consist of three main components:
1. **Mobile Citizen App**: For citizens to report issues with LBS/GPS and track status.
2. **Web Admin Dashboard**: For administrators and SKPD staff to manage and process reports.
3. **Backend API**: The central nervous system handling business logic, notifications, and data storage.

```mermaid
graph TD
    CitizenApp[Mobile Citizen App] -->|HTTPS/REST| API[Backend API]
    AdminWeb[Web Admin Dashboard] -->|HTTPS/REST| API
    API -->|Read/Write| DB[(PostgreSQL)]
    API -->|Send Notifications| FCM[Firebase Cloud Messaging]
    FCM -->|Push Notif| CitizenApp
    FCM -->|Push Notif| AdminWeb
    API -->|Geocoding/Maps| GMap[Google Maps API V3]
```

## Features & Implementation Strategy

### 1. Implementasi LBS & GPS
- **Citizen App**: Use `expo-location` (React Native) to capture latitude and longitude automatically when the user opens the "Kirim Pengaduan" form.
- **Backend**: Store coordinates as a `Geography` type in PostgreSQL (using PostGIS) for efficient spatial queries.

### 2. Integrasi Google Maps API V3
- **Admin Dashboard**: Embed Google Maps to visualize complaint locations.
- **Features**: Heatmaps for complaint density and markers for individual reports.

### 3. Kirim Pengaduan (Send Complaints)
- **Form Fields**: Category (Road, Trash, etc.), Description, Photo Attachment, and Location.
- **File Storage**: Use AWS S3 or Supabase Storage for complaint images.

### 4. Notifikasi Real-time (FCM)
- **Triggers**:
    - New Complaint -> Notify Admin & relevant SKPD.
    - Status Update -> Notify Citizen.
- **Service**: Firebase Cloud Messaging (FCM) for cross-platform push notifications.

### 5. Manajemen SKPD
- **Logic**: Each complaint category is linked to a specific SKPD (Dinas Pekerjaan Umum, Dinas Lingkungan Hidup, etc.).
- **Escalation**: Reports can be manually forwarded by an Admin if the auto-link is incorrect.

### 6. Dashboard Admin (Web-based)
- **Role-based Access**: Super Admin (Total control), SKPD Staff (Only relevant reports).
- **Functionality**: View metrics, generate reports (PDF/Excel), and update handling status.

### 7. Tracking Status
- **Status Workflow**: `Submitted` -> `Verified` -> `In Progress` -> `Resolved` -> `Closed`.
- **History**: Each complaint will have a history log of status changes and notes.

## Proposed Database Schema (Relational)

### `users`
- `id`, `name`, `email`, `role` (CITIZEN, ADMIN, SKPD_STAFF), `fcm_token`

### `skpd` (Satuan Kerja Perangkat Daerah)
- `id`, `name`, `description`, `category_id`

### `categories`
- `id`, `name` (e.g., Infrastruktur, Kebersihan)

### `complaints`
- `id`, `citizen_id`, `category_id`, `skpd_id`, `title`, `description`, `photo_url`, `latitude`, `longitude`, `status`, `created_at`

### `complaint_logs`
- `id`, `complaint_id`, `status_from`, `status_to`, `notes`, `created_at`

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Integration tests for the "Kirim Pengaduan" API flow.
- Mock FCM service to verify notification triggers.
- Unit tests for SKPD assignment logic.

### Manual Verification
- Test GPS coordinate accuracy on physical mobile devices.
- Verify Google Map markers alignment with captured coordinates in the Admin Dashboard.
